The Exceptional Learners Collaborative, 990 Corporate Woods Parkway, Vernon Hills, is conducting a food drive from 9 a.m. to 2 p.m. Tuesday, March 17 through Friday, March 20.

Some of you have reached out to ask how you can contribute. If you have any extra non-perishable food supplies or household items that you would like to donate to help ensure all students in District 103 whose families face financial challenges have their base needs met, the collaborative is looking for the following items specifically:

> Canned Goods
>  Boxed Pastas (noodles/mac & cheese etc…)
> Sauces
> Canned Soups
>  Boxed Cereals
> Cereal/Protein/Granola Bars
> Applesauce
>  Canned Fruit/Vegetables
> Household Items

In times of uncertainty, our community has always rallied to support one another. We appreciate your generosity and commitment to all of our D103 families.

post_text:
Congratulations to first-grade teacher Jenny Larsen who was recognized by the D103 Board of Education this month for renewing her National Board Certification.

The National Board for Professional Teaching Standards is recognized as the "gold standard" in teacher certification. The certification believes higher standards for teachers means better learning for students. By attaining National Board Certification, teachers demonstrate that they are highly accomplished educators who meet high and rigorous standards through intensive study, expert evaluation, self-assessment and peer review.

“Congratulations and thank you, Mrs. Larsen, for renewing your National Board certification and raising the bar for teaching and learning. You are helping to create a climate of professionalism and excellence for our student population by providing the skills needed to succeed” said Dr. Scott Warren, D103 superintendent. In total, the district has 12 National Board Certified teachers.

post_text:
This week is Volunteer Appreciation Week in our Illinois school districts. The Board of Education, at its Tuesday meeting, recognized our District 103 parent organizations, The PTO, Learning Fund Foundation, and Music Boosters, who work countless hours supporting our staff, student and parent community.

“We cherish our partnership and want to recognize the leadership of our three volunteer organizations help to make District 103 Leaders in Learning!” said Superintendent Scott Warren.

post_text: Our Daniel Wright student council has been collecting donations to support a local not-for-profit organization, “Loving without Limits”. The mission of Lw/oL is to provide caregivers of hospitalized children with “care bags” over the Mother's Day weekend. Each $10 donation goes to purchase a blanket for the care bag. This year’s goal is to support seven local area hospitals. To make a donation, please visit ~ https://www.lovingwithoutlimits.org/ ~. In the special instructions area, please note DW Student Council fundraiser.

shared_text:
Adlai E. Stevenson High School
November 12, 2018 at 10:58 AM ·

In observance of Veterans Day, we recognize Stevenson alumni and staff who have served. We also recall this reunion that occurred last year when Marine Corps Pfc. Jeffery Harris III, a 2015 alumnus, arrived at Stevenson for a surprise visit.

Pfc. Harris is scheduled to deploy to Iraq in April. He will be home for the holidays and his family is seeking support from the community to give him a memorable send-off. https://www.gofundme.com/1st-born-son-graduates-from-usmc?fbclid=IwAR1J-l6sWwcAvEVaVpDW-3B6qz70kL66ENtQ9_WKqEm3Puai51YL6DKROvQ
